Material Information Summary – Ballard Mining (ASX: BM1) – Mt Ida Gold Project Update (22 July 2025)

Key Highlights

  1. Drilling Program Underway
  2. Three rigs currently active (1 diamond, 2 RC).
  3. Fourth RC rig to mobilize within 2 weeks, accelerating exploration.

  4. Planned 130,000m drill program (50,000m exploration, 80,000m infill at Baldock).

  5. Exploration Targets

  6. 18 high-priority targets identified across 26km of prospective strike.

  7. Targets refined using recent high-resolution drone mag survey.

  8. Mineral Resource & Development

  9. JORC-compliant resource: 10.3Mt @ 3.3g/t Au (1.1Moz).
  10. Baldock deposit (84% of resource): 4.1Moz @ 930koz; advanced for near-term development.

  11. Mining approvals secured for open pit/underground at Baldock.

  12. Capital & Funding

  13. IPO raised $30M (oversubscribed); funds allocated to exploration/development.

  14. $4M loan (pre-IPO) repaid from proceeds.

  15. Next Steps

  16. Phase 1 exploration + infill drilling at Baldock.
  17. DFS-level metallurgical/geotechnical studies.
  18. Assay results expected in coming weeks.

Material Information Summary (ASX: M4M - Macro Metals Limited)

Key Highlights:

  • Strategic Acquisition: Macro Metals and WA Limestone jointly acquired the Derby East Construction Sands Project (100% interest) for A$125,000 (A$62,000 each).
  • Location & Infrastructure:
  • 24km east of Port of Derby (all-weather road access).
  • Contains two granted exploration licences (E04/2390, E04/2478) spanning ~60 km².
  • Market Opportunity:
  • Sand meets Singapore’s import standards (150M tonnes imported 2020-2023) and WA Main Roads Spec 302.
  • NORDEN Shipping (Macro’s partner) holds a Singapore sand import licence, aiding logistics.
  • Resource Potential:
  • Drilling (1,604.7m) confirms construction-grade sand (7-60m depth, avg. thickness 39m).
  • Golders geotechnical tests confirm non-plastic, low-fines sand with CBR values of 20-30%.
  • Next Steps:
  • Mineral Resource definition and regulatory approvals underway.
  • Logistics planning for transhipment via Port of Derby to SE Asian markets.

Material Information Summary – Aeris Resources (ASX: AIS)

FY26 Production & Financial Guidance

  • Production (FY26 Guidance vs FY25 Actual):
  • Copper: 24–29kt (vs 24.9kt)
  • Gold: 44–56koz (vs 55.2koz)
  • Silver: 240–293koz (vs 185.2koz)
  • Copper Equivalent: 40–49kt (vs 42.1kt)
  • Costs & Capital (FY26 Guidance):
  • Mine Operating Costs: $302–369M
  • Sustaining Capital: $57–70M
  • Growth Capital: $65–80M
  • Exploration Spend: $18–23M (double FY25)
  • Cash Position: $49.5M (end-Q4 FY25).

Operational Highlights

  • Tritton (Copper):
  • FY26 production guidance up 37% (midpoint) vs FY25.
  • Mill to run above capacity (2Mtpa) in H2 FY26 due to Murrawombie Pit ore.
  • Constellation project (7.6Mt at 2.01% Cu) advancing; major spend from FY27.
  • Cracow (Gold):
  • FY26 production guidance 36–46koz (lower grade offset by higher throughput).
  • Exploring Golden Plateau for bulk tonnage potential.

Strategic Initiatives

  • Divestment: North Queensland assets (952km²) in process; may release $6.5M in bonds.
  • Debt Reduction: $40M WHSP term facility extended to August 2026; asset sales to accelerate repayment.
  • Exploration Focus:
  • Tritton: 80,000m drilling targeting extensions at Avoca Tank/Budgerygar.
  • Jaguar: Testing 8 base-metal targets; reducing care costs to $600k/quarter.
  • Stockman: Seeking partner for high-grade polymetallic project (13.4Mt at 2.1% Cu, 4.2% Zn).

Key Risks/Material Changes

  • Declining Grades: Cracow gold output impacted by lower grades (offset by exploration).
  • Capital Intensity: FY26 growth capex ($65–80M) focuses on Tritton (Murrawombie pre-strip).
